## External Dependencies

| Dependency | Type | Source |
|------------|------|--------|
| **jQuery** | JS | WordPress bundled |
| **Font Awesome 5.15.4** | CSS | CDN (cdnjs) |
| **Google Fonts** (Roboto) | CSS | Google CDN |
| **Alphacorsa Font** | CSS | onlinewebfonts.com |
| **ACF (Advanced Custom Fields)** | Plugin | Required (fields defined but plugin not installed) |

> [!CAUTION]
> **ACF is not installed** in `wp-content/plugins/`. The `acf-fields.php` include will silently fail (`if (function_exists('acf_add_local_field_group'))` guard). The CPTs will work, but custom fields won't be available in the admin until ACF is installed.

---

## Key Observations & Issues

### ⚠️ Issues Found

1. **Duplicate enqueue file** — `inc/enqueue-scripts.php` registers the same assets with different handles as `functions.php`, potentially causing double-loading or conflicts
2. **ACF plugin missing** — Custom field groups are defined but ACF isn't installed
3. **Empty template parts** — 8 of 10 template parts are empty; all logic is hardcoded in main templates
4. **Empty page templates** — `page-games.php`, `page-live-sports.php`, `page-reservation.php` are empty stubs
5. **Hardcoded phone/email** — `+919876543210` and `hello@knockout.in` are placeholder values hardcoded in header and footer
6. **Hardcoded address** — `123 Park Street, Kolkata - 700016` is a placeholder
7. **`flush_rewrite_rules()` on every init** — Called on every page load inside `sports_cafe_register_post_types()`, which is a performance issue (should only flush on activation)
8. **Social links are `#` placeholders** — Footer social links point to `#`
9. **Footer links use absolute paths** (`/about`, `/menu`) instead of `home_url()` — will break on subdirectory installs
10. **Mouse trail script in footer** — Inline JS creating DOM elements on every `mousemove` can impact performance

### ✅ Things Done Well

1. **Clean design system** — Well-organized CSS variables for consistent theming
2. **Auto page creation** — Theme automatically creates key pages with correct templates on activation
3. **Primary menu auto-setup** — Creates and assigns the navigation menu on theme activation
4. **Proper script localization** — AJAX URL and nonce properly localized
5. **Responsive design** — Separate responsive CSS and mobile menu implementation
6. **Gutenberg support** — All CPTs have `show_in_rest` enabled
7. **Conditional CSS loading** — Page-template-specific styles only load on relevant pages

